      <hedline>
        <hl1>Study on Polar Flights</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A joint Canadian-Russian study has found that opening air traffic routes over the North Pole to thousands of commercial flights a year is ''feasible and desirable.'' Aviation experts said the study, to be released today, lays the groundwork for an increase in the number of polar flights and may make practical nonstop flights between far-flung cities.</p>
        <p>Business Day, Page C1.</p>
      </block>
